        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 15 at 8:18PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 818 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 17
miles northwest of Pritchett, or 28 miles west of Springfield, moving
east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Baca,
northeastern Las Animas and southeastern Bent Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
